sql:
SELECT AVG(gpa) AS average_gpa
FROM academic_records
WHERE semester = 'Fall' AND year = 2022;

SELECT COUNT(student_id)
FROM mental_health_records
WHERE depression_status = 'severe';

external_knowledge:
- A high GPA generally indicates better academic performance; 
- A higher class year signifies a more advanced academic standing within the institution; 
- The most recent records are likely to provide an accurate and up-to-date representation of a student's current situation.
